                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d161">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5131/1027b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Straus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-10T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 10, 1934—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>492. Mr. Sayre this morning handed French Ambassador the <hi rend="italic"
                        >aide-mémoire</hi> quoted in our 482, December 4, 9 p.m. At the same time he
                    took occasion to emphasize the importance of early ratification of the double
                    taxation treaty, pointing out that there was a group in the government which
                    wished to make this ratification a condition precedent to negotiations; that no
                    mention had been made of the treaty in our <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>
                    but that if action were not shortly forthcoming the above opinion might come to
                    prevail. The Ambassador is further telegraphing on the possibility of concluding
                    a <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> as outlined to you pending a more
                    comprehensive trade agreement. It is possible that you will be approached on one
                    or more phases of this interview.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
